        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúI was very used to Pennsylvania law and structure and how unions can and should run,‚Äù she said. ‚ÄúSeeing what the employees in Madison go through and the rights they don‚Äôt have was just astounding. It was evident how little say they have in the work they do. I met a nurse who was fired for concerted activity for the work that I do often. It made me have a deep appreciation for the rights I have as a union employee.‚Äù",
